@NODE "intro" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Introduction"
@PREV "main"
@NEXT "req"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

 This program is a easy-to-use user address book manager, with
 (I hope) some nice features.

 I had a lots of notes with my friends' phone numbers.
 And they where everywhere, but when I needed them, I
 couldn't find them (as usual).

 So I decided to make a program for all my addresses and
 phone-numbers, etc. This program is the result.


 @{b}@{u}Features@{uu}@{ub}

 This programs features :

 À Simple GUI, for easy usage for everyone (I hope).

 À Fast and easy to use.

 À DTMF-tones when dialing phone-numbers
 À Send emails (if the email program is running...)
 À Check homepages.
 À Copy & Paste with clipboard.
 À Append saved base-files to each other.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "req" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Requirements"
@PREV "intro"
@NEXT "install"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

 This program needs following stuff:

 À An Amiga (ohh gosh, you can't mean that) :-)
 À AmigaDOS 2.04 or higher..
 À Asl.library...
 À tabs.gadget placed under "SYS:Classes/Gadgets/"  (Included in archive)
   @{b}
   The .gadget and .image files are:
   Copyright (c) 1994 Commodore-Amiga, Inc.
   And discussed further in Classes/GI1.Readme and Classes/GI1.License.
   @{ub}
 À AmigaDOS 3.x or higher to use the locale-support (not required).



 That's it !.. And a little memory to :-)

 This program has been tested on following systems with success:

 Amiga 4000 (AmigaOS 3.5, CyberStorm-MkII, CV3D, 2 Mb Chip/96 Mb Fast),
 Amiga 4000 (AmigaOS 3.5, CyberStorm-PPC, PII+, 2 Mb Chip/62 Mb Fast),
 Amiga 1200 (AmigaOS 3.5, Blizzard-PPC, BVision, 2 Mb Chip/40 MB Fast)

 @{b}Tested software (through communication)@{ub} :

 Email : AEmail 1.51 (beta)
         Iris 1.9
         Voodoo 1.427 (demo)
         YAM 1.3.5
         YAM 2.0

 Web-browsers : AWeb II 3.3 Full version
                IBrowse 2.0 Full version
                IProbe 0.7 (Beta)
                Voyager 3 (and 2.95 NG) Registered

                OpenURL.library 2.x (Can be utilized if available)...
                

 @{b}Untested software (but supported)@{ub} :

 Email : Eucalyptus,
         AmigaMail (OS 3.5)

 Web-browser(s) : AMosaic


@ENDNODE

@NODE "install" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Installation"
@PREV "req"
@NEXT "usage"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

 This program can be used without installation, but
 the installer-script makes the job really easy.

 The installer script will ask you where to create a OnyxBase-drawer
 (If it already exist, the installer will make a backup of the old drawer)

 You can also install (if you want to) a catalog file with your native language.
 German and Swedish catalog files is supplied with this version, but there will be
 more in future versions of OnyxBase..


 If there is any problems with this, please contact me...

 @{b}Notice! the locale support needs AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher to work...@{ub}

@ENDNODE

