 Keyboard-shortcuts :

 All of the buttons have shortcut-keys.
 It's easy to see which letter it is because it is underlined,
 such as "A" on the @{b}@{u}A@{uu}dd@{ub}-button, "D" on the @{b}@{u}D@{uu}elete@{ub}-button and etc..
   
 À Add..........."a"
 À Delete........"d"
 À Sort.........."s"
 À Search........"r"
 À Dial.........."i"
 À Email........."e"
 À Homepage......"h"
 À Preferences..."p"

 NOTICE! - shortcut keys might differ with other languages than the one built-in.
  
@ENDNODE


@NODE "usage-gui-add" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Add)"
@PREV "usage-gui"
@NEXT "usage-gui-del"

 @{b}@{u}Add an entry@{uu}@{ub}

 À If you want to add a user in the database, simply press the @{b}Add@{ub}-button.
   You can also choose it as a menu choice...

   Then a new listning is created (without any contents).
   The new record will be showed in the listview as "-no name-".
   This will change as soon as you enter the name of the user.

 À Fill out the information you want, then the new record is ready.
 
 À If you want to add more entries, jump to the first point.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-del" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Delete)"
@PREV "usage-gui-add"
@NEXT "usage-gui-sort"

 @{b}@{u}Delete an entry@{uu}@{ub}

 À To delete a record simply click on it in the listview or use the cursor key
   to highlight the correct entry.
   After that, press the @{b}Delete@{ub}-button or the underscored (shortcut)
   letter for the delete-button.

   You can also choose it as a menu choice...

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-sort" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Sort)"
@PREV "usage-gui-del"
@NEXT "usage-gui-search"

 @{b}@{u}Sort items (records)@{uu}@{ub}

 À If the contents in the database are more than 1, then it's possible
   to sort the contents.
   The sort algorythm in this version is pretty primitive, but it works
   as it should (i hope) ;-).. 

 À After the @{b}Sort@{ub}-button been pressed, a requester will show 3 choices.
   Lastname, Firstname or Cancel. Lastname will sort the database after the
   users lastnames. The firstname-choice will do the same but with the
   firstnames. (easy isn't it ?). 

 À And the third and last choice will cancel the whole sort-operation.


 * If it's used from menu or shortcut keys, there will be no requester.


 Shortcut keys :

 À Firstname -> RAmiga + "F"
 À Lastname  -> RAmiga + "L"


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-search" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Search)"
@PREV "usage-gui-sort"
@NEXT "usage-gui-dial"

 @{b}@{u}Search item (record)@{uu}@{ub}

 À If the contents in the database are more than 1, then it's possible
   to search through the contents.
   The search algorythm in this version is pretty primitive, but it works
   kind of/somehow (i hope) ;-)..

 À If you activate this from the main GUI, the default search is set to
   "Lastname", which is easy changed with the cycle gadget.

 À If you use the sub-menus you can get to the right search mode directly.


 Usage :

 - Choose what you want to search after (use the cycle gadget)

 - Enter a string to search for (in the string gadget)

 - The press "Search from top" to search from the first item or
   "Search from cursor" to search from the current position.


 NOTICE!

 * The "whole record"-search is VERY primitive!, so don't rely to much on it :)


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-dial" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Dial)"
@PREV "usage-gui-search"
@NEXT "usage-gui-mail"

 @{b}@{u}Dial@{uu}@{ub}

 À This button dials the number that is presented in the phone-entry (if any),
   using DTMF-tones in the speakers.
   Place the phone near the speaker and then press this button.
   If everything is ok, the number should be dialed, check @{" FAQ " LINK "faq"} - section otherwise.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-mail" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Email)"
@PREV "usage-gui-dial"
@NEXT "usage-gui-page"

 @{b}@{u}Email@{uu}@{ub}

 The function of this button is to send email to the address in the record (if any).

 À First, ensure you have set the mail-program you want to use. This is
   done in the @{" preferences " LINK "usage-gui-prefs"} - section.

 À You must start the mail-program (this will be changed in future versions
   of OnyxBase).

 À Click on the @{b}Email@{ub}-button and if it's all ok, it should work.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-page" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Homepage)"
@PREV "usage-gui-mail"
@NEXT "usage-gui-prefs"

 @{b}@{u}Homepage@{uu}@{ub}

 The function of this button is to send the URL (if any) in the record to a
 web browser.

 À First, ensure you have set the specific web-browser you want to use. This is
   done in the @{" preferences " LINK "usage-gui-prefs"} - section.

 À Start the web-browser (I will also change this in future versions..)

 À Click on the @{b}Homepage@{ub}-button and if it's all ok, this should work too.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-gui-prefs" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (GUI-Preferences)"
@PREV "usage-gui-page"
@NEXT "usage-gui"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Preferences@{uu}@{ub}

 +---+-----------------------------------------------------------+--+
 | À | OnyxBase - Preferences...                                 |  |
 +---+-----------------------------------------------------------+--+
 |+-------------------------++-------------------------------------+|
 ||Visual in GUI :          || Email program :      [   AEMail    ]||
 ||                         ||                                     ||
 || +--/                    || Web browser :        [   Amosaic   ]||
 || |\\/| Nickname           ||                                     ||
 || +--+                    || Open URL on :        [ *Requester* ]||
 || +--/                    ||                                     ||
 || |\\/| 2:nd address field || On double-click :    [  Do nothing ]||
 || +--+                    ||                                     ||
 || +--/                    ||                                     ||
 || |\\/| Email              ||-------------------------------------||
 || +--+                    ||                                     ||
 || +--/                    || Dial delay :         [ 0.05 second ]||
 || |\\/| URL                ||                                     ||
 || +--+                    || Speaker :            [     Left    ]||
 || +--/                    ||                                     ||
 || |\\/| Phone              || Audio priority :     [      0      ]||
 || +--+                    ||                                     ||
 || +--/                    ||                                     ||
 || |\\/| Other              ||                                     ||
 || +--+                    ||                                     ||
 ||                         ||                                     ||
 ||                         ||-------------------------------------||
 ||-------------------------||      +--/                           ||
 ||                         ||      |\\/| Save files with icon      ||
 ||                         ||      +--+                           ||
 ||                         ||      +--/                           ||
 ||                         ||      |\\/| Ask before delete item    ||
 ||                         ||      +--+                           ||
 ||                         ||      +--/                           ||
 ||                         ||      |\\/| Show quit requester       ||
 ||                         ||      +--+                           ||
 || +--/                    ||      +--/ +-----------------+ +----+||
 || |\\/| Name in position   ||      |\\/| |                 | | << |||
 || +--+                    ||      +--+ +-----------------+ +----+||
 |+-------------------------++-------------------------------------+|
 |+--------------------++--------------------++--------------------+|        
 ||        Save        ||         Use        ||       Cancel       ||
 |+--------------------++--------------------++--------------------+|                                  
 +------------------------------------------------------------------+


 @{b}The new GUI looks a little different compared to the one above.
 The contents of the preference GUI is however the same, only
 spread out on 2 "tab" choices for space reasons :-)@{ub}


 * Visual in GUI :

   The checkmarks represents the field which is going to be shown in the
   main-GUI of OnyxBase... (Some might don't use all fields, then they can
   easy be removed here.

   À If "Name in position" is checked, the name of the highlighted item
     will be shown in the main-GUI (down with the position).
 

 * Email program :

   This cycle gadget will let you set the email program that OnyxBase
   is going to communicate with when the "Email"-button is pressed in the
   main-GUI.
 
   Following e-mail clients are supported :

   À AEmail
   À AmigaMail
   À Eucalytus
   À Iris
   À Voodoo
   À YAM 1.3.x
   À YAM 2.x


 * Web browser :

   This cycle gadget will let you set the web browser that OnyxBase
   is going to communicate with when the "Homepage"-button is pressed
   in the main-GUI.
 
   Following web browsers are supported :

   À Amosaic
   À AWeb
   À IBrowse
   À IProbe
   À Voyager(NG)

   À OpenURL.library (If available)
     This will also automatically start the browser (if not started earlier).

 * Open URL on :

   This is an option how the URL will be sent and shown to the web browser.
   You can either send it to the current active window or a totaly new one.

   This cycle gadget has following options :

   À *Requester* (Lets you decide between New window or Active window)
   À New window
   À Active window


 * On double-click :

   This will let you choose what is going to happen if you double-click
   on a name in the listview (the list with names).

   The cycle gadget has following options :

   À Do nothing
   À Dial number
   À Send email
   À Check URL


 * Dial delay :

   This sets the delay time between each tone, when you have pressed the
   "Dial"-button in the main-GUI.

   The options are :

   À No delay
   À 0.05 second
   À 0.5 second
   À 1 second
   À 2 seconds


 * Speaker :

   This let you choose which speaker the tone(s) (noise) will play in.

   The options are :

   À Left
   À Right


 * Audio priority :

   This gadget let you set the priority on audio.device when it's in use
   from OnyxBase. You can change this if something else is using the device
   at the same time, to get the control over device when playing sounds.
   (This is yet very little tested, sorry for that...)

   The options are :

   À -1 (Lowest priority)
   À 0
   À 1
   À 127 (Highest priority)
 

 * Save files with icon :

   This option will enable the program to save an icon with the file.
   This icon will carry some information about the file and has also
   a default tool (The program itself + path).


 * Ask before delete item :

   If this is enabled you will have to confirm everytime you want to delete
   an item in the list.


 * Show quit requester :

   If this is enabled, the program ask everytime you quit the program if that
   is what you really want to do (so you don't miss unsaved data etc.)


 * The last option (unnamed) :

   This is an option to choose a database file to be loaded when the program
   is executed (if you have a favourite database for example).

   Notice! - Both WB-arguments and CLI-arguments will override this option.


 After choosing the settings, you can either @{b}save@{ub} them or @{b}use@{ub}
 them temporarily. When pressing the @{b}save@{ub}-button, you also save the
 position of the windows.


 À Shortcut keys : "s" = Save
                   "u" = Use
                   "c" = Cancel





 @{" Back to previous menu " LINK "usage-gui"}

@ENDNODE

