@NODE "usage-editing" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Editing)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-loadsave"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Edit an entry@{uu}@{ub}

 À To edit an entry, simply click on it in the listview or use the cursor key
   to highlight the desired entry.

 À Then simply edit the string gadgets (whichever you want to change).
   That's it.


 * Tips! - When a string gadget is active, you can jump to next one using
   the TAB-key. To get to the previous one use Shift+TAB...


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-loadsave" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Load/Save)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-newproject"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Load/Save@{uu}@{ub}

 * Load :

   Select a file using the ASL-requester.
   If there is any active posts (items) in the adressbook you will
   be asked if you want to clear the adressbook or want to append
   the new data to it.

   Note 1 - You can also drag & drop a file on the main window
            of OnyxBase to load it!

   Note 2 - You can start OnyxBase from CLI with a argument
            of the filename you want to load.

   Note 3 - Mark the Adress book (file) from workbench and
            start OnyxBase with the icon (by pressing shift) and the
            file will load too (if everything goes right).

 * Save :

   Choose a file with the ASL-requester... That's it ;-)
   (The .onx extension will automatically be added to the file!)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-newproject" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (New project)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-importexport"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - New project@{uu}@{ub}

 Use this if you want to clear the current project.
 If there is any items in the current project, you will be asked if
 you want to save the data or clear it...

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-importexport" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Import/Export)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-information"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Import/Export@{uu}@{ub}


   @{i}Note that all of these formats are not completely same..
   This might lead (durig export/import) that some some fields can
   be removed, so it's always smart to backup the old (if any) file
   before replacing it...@{ui}


 * Import :

   Select a file using the ASL-requster (can't be any easier).
   The program will tell you if everything went well or not.
   If there is any active posts (items) in the adressbook you will
   be asked if you want to clear the adressbook or want to append
   the new data to it.

   The supported formats are :

   À OnyxBase 1.x
   À MegaBook 4.x
   À YAM 2.x


 * Export :

   Choose a file with the ASL-requester... That's it ;-)

   The supported formats are :

   À OnyxBase 1.x
   À MegaBook 4.x
   À YAM 2.x

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-printing" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Printing)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-information"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Printing@{uu}@{ub}

 +---+---------------------------------+--+--+
 | À | Print...                        |  |  |
 +---+---------------------------------+--+--+
 |+-----------------------------------------+|
 || +--/                                    ||
 || |\\/| Show labels                        ||
 || +--+                                    ||
 ||                     +---+      +---+    ||
 || [  Range  ]   From: | 1 |  To: | 2 |    ||
 ||                     +---+      +---+    ||
 |+-----------------------------------------+|
 || +--/                    +--/            ||
 || |\\/| Nickname           |\\/| Country    ||
 || +--+                    +--+            ||
 || +--/                    +--/            ||
 || |\\/| Address            |\\/| Email      ||
 || +--+                    +--+            ||
 || +--/                    +--/            ||
 || |\\/| 2:nd Address       |\\/| URL        ||
 || +--+                    +--+            ||
 || +--/                    +--+            ||
 || |\\/| Zip code           |\\/| Phone      ||
 || +--+                    +--+            ||
 || +--/                    +--/            ||
 || |\\/| City               |\\/| Other      ||
 || +--+                    +--+            ||
 |+-----------------------------------------+|
 |+--------------------++-------------------+|
 ||        Print       ||      Cancel       ||
 |+--------------------++-------------------+|
 +-------------------------------------------+


 * Show labels :

   If this checkmark is ticked then the label of all fields will be printed
   before the actual information.

   Name     : Stefan Blixth
   Nickname : Develin

   ^^^^^^^^^^
   
 * All / Range :

   This will let you choose between printing all post or just a range of them.

   If Range is selected, you can specify from which post you want to start printing
   from and to which post that going to be the last one in the range.

 * All the other Ticks :

   Specifies which fields that going to be printed...
   Notice! - Firstname and Lastname are always printed.

 * Print / Cancel :

   Will do exactly what the say ;-)

   Notice! - In this current version of OnyxBase (2.1) the control of the printing
   is a little weak. In other words you cannot break a queued print and if you
   havn't got a printer (or has turned it off) you will have a "fun" time pressing
   the requester telling you to check the cables on the printer etc...
   (It will dissapear after many many press on the cancel button)
   This will be fixed as soon as possible ;-) (sorry inconvenience).

@ENDNODE

