@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-copypaste" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Copy & Paste)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-moveupdown"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Copy & Paste fields@{uu}@{ub}

 This will let you copy from or paste to the desired field.
 You can also copy or paste a whole record at once.


        Copy - Shortkeys                   Paste - Shortkeys

 À Firstname    -> RAmiga + 1       À Firstname    -> RAmiga + !
 À Lastname     -> RAmiga + 2       À Lastname     -> RAmiga + "
 À Nickname     -> RAmiga + 3       À Nickname     -> RAmiga + ú
 À Address      -> RAmiga + 4       À Address      -> RAmiga + $
 À 2:nd Address -> RAmiga + 5       À 2:nd Address -> RAmiga + %
 À Zip code     -> RAmiga + 6       À Zip code     -> RAmiga + &
 À City/State   -> RAmiga + 7       À City/State   -> RAmiga + /
 À Country      -> RAmiga + 8       À Country      -> RAmiga + (
 À Email        -> RAmiga + 9       À Email        -> RAmiga + )
 À URL          -> RAmiga + 0       À URL          -> RAmiga + =
 À Phone        -> RAmiga + +       À Phone        -> RAmiga + ?
 À Other        -> RAmiga + \\       À Other        -> RAmiga + |

 À Whole Record -> RAmiga + C       À Whole Record -> RAmiga + V



 Notice! - You can't use the "external" clipboard when pasting a whole
           record, it's right now only used internal when you copy
           a whole record from OnyxBase...
           You can however paste a whole record to "other" places after
           you have copied it from OnyxBase.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-moveupdown" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Moving items)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-items"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Moving items (records)@{uu}@{ub}

 This will let you move a record up or down (in position).


 Shortcut keys :

 À Up   -> RAmiga + U  or  Left cursor key
 À Down -> RAmiga + D  or  Right cursor key


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-items" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Go to items)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage-other"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Go to items (records)@{uu}@{ub}

 With this sub-menu you can jump to next/previous item or
 the first/last in the project.


 Shortcut keys :

 À Next item     -> RAmiga + "."  or  Cursor key (Down)
 À Previous item -> RAmiga + ","  or  Cursor key (Up)
 À First item    -> RAmiga + "<"
 À Last item     -> RAmiga + ">"


@ENDNODE

@NODE "usage-other" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Usage (Other)"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "usage"

 @{b}@{u}Usage - Other@{uu}@{ub}

 ARexx :

 À No active commands yet available, wait until next release of OnyxBase...

@ENDNODE

@NODE "faq" "OnyxBase 2.1 - FAQ"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "news"

@{b}@{u}FAQ - Frequently Asked Question@{uu}@{ub}

* @{b}Q = Question@{ub}
* @{b}A = Answer@{ub}

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q - I have installed the catalog file but I can't get the program
    to work in my native language... why ?

A - First of all.. Do you have AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher ?
    If so, check if the file @{b}locale.library@{ub} is present under @{b}SYS:Libs/@{ub}
    Still doesn't work ?.. Start @{b}locale@{ub} under @{b}SYS:prefs/@{ub} and
    check if you actually chosen your native language.

    If this still refuses to work.. Try to reboot your computer and start
    the program again.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q - The program says - @{b}Can not communicate with ......!@{ub} when I try to go to
    go to a homepage from OnyxBase... why ?

A - In this version you must have the browser (or email-program) started first
    before you can go to a homepage (or email address). OnyxBase tries to find
    the AREXX-interface for the program, and if unable to it, you get this
    message.

    If you actually started the browser (or email-program) and get such
    message, check in the preferences that you actually chosen the right
    browser (or email-program).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q - The @{" Dial " LINK "usage-gui-dial"} - feature in the program does not work as
    it should. I hear the sound, but the telephone does not "hear" it.

A - Make sure to have a normal volume on the speaker, not to much, not to
    little. It is very important to have the right level on the volume.
    
    Check if you hear it in the correct speaker ;-).. check the @{" Preferences " LINK "usage-gui-prefs"}
    section where you can choose left or right speaker.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q - I can not hear any sound when I try to dial the number.. why ?

A - Do you have anything else using the audio.device in the background ?
    If so, check if this has higher priority than OnyxBase's dialer.
    You can change the priority in the @{" Preferences " LINK "usage-gui-prefs"} - section.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@ENDNODE

@NODE "news" "OnyxBase 2.1 - What's new?"
@PREV "usage"
@NEXT "history"

 @{b}@{u}What's new@{uu}@{ub}

 À Added printing option. (Could be better though, working on it...)

 À Fixed a long standing problem with handling WB-arguments.

 À Changed the Preferences-GUI a little, now using tabs (it was to huge).

 À Removed all Enforcer hits I could find ;-)

 À OpenURL.library can now be utilized (starts the browser for you).

 À Fixed a problem when the default-tool should have been added to
   the saved icon (It worked from CLI but not in WB mode).

 À Updated the current locale files for version 2.1

 À Added 2 new languages thanks to Boleslav Kristen (Czech) and
   Jesper Dam Andersen (Danish).

 À The MB-exporter should now export version 4.00 and not 4.10 when
   there is no country fields in the database.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "history" "OnyxBase 2.1 - History"
@PREV "news"
@NEXT "future"

 @{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

 À 26-03-1998 - Start coding on this project.
                It's been delayed so many times because of school and so..


 À 23-07-1998 - First public release (1.0) of OnyxBase :

              À DTMF tones when dialing (using audio.device).
              À Communication with email and web-browser programs.
              À Copy & Past feature through clipboard.device.
              À Full locale support.


 À 19-07-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 1) :

              À Gosh! what a year goes by fast ;-/
              À It now even gives you back all the memory it takes ;-)


 À 21-07-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 2) :

              À The exe is now 20+ kb smaller...
              À + Some other changes...


 À 24-07-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 3) :

              À Added an extra address field (for Americans etc..)
              À Changed the fileformat (because of the extra filed).
              À The program can now save a icon (with info).
              À The text "Post" is now renamed "Items" ;-D


 À 01-08-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 4) :

              À Now supports Drag'n drop..
              À Can export to MegaBook 4.x, Yam 2.x and OnyxBase 1.x
              À Handles both WB and CLI arguments.
              À Now also includes a DirectoryOpus file type (for Opus users)


 À 04-08-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 5) :

              À The text doesn't break the window border anymore!
              À The path and the name of OnyxBase (the name it has on the
                disk) is now saved in the icon, so it will be executed when
                you double-click on the icon of an ".onx"-file...
              À Fixed a problem with the second address field
                (wasn't shaded when it was supposed to be (lame me!) ;-D
              À Added the second address field in the copy/paste menu...

 À 22-09-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 6) :

              À Import of YAM 2.x, MegaBook 4.x and OnyxBase 1.x is now possible...

 À 08-11-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 7) :

              À Copy/Past whole records are now possible
              À The .onx-format (2.0) slightly changed.
              À At last! a real DTMF generator instead of samples ;-)
              À Optimized the menu a little (Thanks to Andreas Kuerzinger for the advice) ;-)

 À 11-11-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 8) :
              À Changed the layout a little in the main GUI (position).
              À Hopefully fixed a strange bug when activating the prefs.-section.
              À It's now possible to search in a whole record. (every field at once)

 À 21-11-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 9) :
              À Added locale support + a swedish locale catalog.
              À Fixed some rather stupid bugs.

 À 09-12-1999 - OnyxBase 2.0 (Public Beta 10) :
              À Added a german locale catalog (Thanks to Andreas Kuerzinger).
              À The GUI now works dynamic as it should do, at last :)
              À Fixed the loss of some data-fields when importing/exporting from Megabook.

 À 13-12-1999 - Second public release (2.0) of OnyxBase :
              À Fixed the last pieces in the program...
              À Added a new documtation (amigaguide).
              À Added a Installer.

              À The whole program has been totaly re-written. (since 1.0)
              À Replaced the browser "Mindwalker" with IProbe...
              À Fixed a bug when communicating with AWeb.
              À Integrated an DTMF-generator (instead of samples).
              À New file format (Binary).
              À You can now search in the list of users...
              À Added support for Iris...

 À 22-12-1999 - Third public release (2.01) of OnyxBase :

              À Added a option to autostart a database (from prefs-GUI).
              À It's not necessary to press Save + Use in preferences any more.
              À Fixed some strings in the cycle-gadget (Amosaic -> AMosaic) :-)
              À Fixed a bug in the string-date (used in the information window).
              À The path + filename should now be remembered if the database was
                started from the icon (with OnyxBase as default tool).


 À 30-12-1999 - Fourth public release (2.02) of OnyxBase :

              À Forgot to terminate the creation of the prefs-GUI,
                this would lead to lockup of the program. - (should now be fixed)


 À 08-03-2000 - Release - Version 2.1 :

              À Added printing option. (Could be better though, working on it...)
              À Fixed a long standing problem with handling WB-arguments.
              À Changed the preferences GUI a little, now using tabs (it was to huge).
              À Removed all Enforcer hits I could find ;-)
              À OpenURL.library can now be utilized (starts the browser for you).
              À Fixed a problem when the default-tool should have been added to
                the saved icon (It worked from CLI but not in WB mode).
              À Updated the current locale files for version 2.1
              À Added 2 new languages thanks to Boleslav Kristen (Czech) and
                Jesper Dam Andersen (Danish).
              À The MB-exporter should now export version 4.00 and not 4.10 when
                there is no country fields in the database.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "future" "OnyxBase 2.1 - Future"
@PREV "history"
@NEXT "copy"

 @{b}@{u}Future@{uu}@{ub}

 À Useable ARexx interface (it's allready there, but no commands are supported yet).

 À Fix the lousy search and sort functions ;-)

 À Let a modem dial the number (for us lazy people).

 À Make a better print solution (better control).

 À More programs to communicate with.

 À Import & Export databases from different programs.

 À Enable startup email program if such isn't started.

 À Try to optimize it some more.

 À AHI-support (for the dialing),if there is someone who need it ? (contact me).


 À You could write a letter to me and tell me what you are missing,
   and I see if I can make your wishes come true ;-)

@ENDNODE

